{"type":"route","meta":{"status":200,"headers":{"content-type":"text/markdown","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/[[...slug]]/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/[[...slug]]/route,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/sales/content.md"}},"body":"# Sales Hub (/docs/sales)\n\n\n\nThe Sales Hub is your complete record of everything that's been sold or paid for. Click **Sales** in the left menu and you'll see a sidebar with eight sections. Each one is focused on a different part of your business and has its own search, date filter, and **Export** button.\n\n***\n\nDaily Sales [#daily-sales]\n\n**Sales → Daily Sales**\n\nYour end-of-day summary. Use the **Today*&#x2A;, &#x2A;*\\<*&#x2A;, and &#x2A;*>** buttons to pick any day and see a full breakdown of what happened.\n\nThe page is split into three parts:\n\n**Transaction summary**\nA table showing what was sold by item type (e.g., Service, Product), how many were sold, and the net total.\n\n**Cash movement summary**\nA breakdown of how payments were collected — showing each payment method (Cash, Online, Card, etc.) and the amount collected through each. Also shows the total **Payments collected** and how much of that was **tips**.\n\n**Summary bar**\nFour quick-view numbers at the bottom:\n\n* **Total Sales** — total revenue for the day\n* **Total Transactions** — number of completed transactions\n* **Sale Types** — how many different item types were sold\n* **Payment Methods** — how many different payment methods were used\n\n***\n\nAppointments [#appointments]\n\n**Sales → Appointments**\n\nA full list of every appointment-based sale. Use this when you need to look up a specific service, client visit, or check what was charged and whether a discount was applied.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Client (name + phone) · Service · Sale Date · Team Member · Unit Price · Quantity · Discount · Total Price\n\nDiscounts show in red when applied. Search by client name or service, or filter by date range. Click **Export** to download as CSV.\n\n***\n\nSales Transactions [#sales-transactions]\n\n**Sales → Sales**\n\nYour complete transaction history across all sale types. By default it shows the last 30 days.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Payment Date · Client · Team Members · Payment Method · Tips · Status · Amount\n\nThe **Status** column shows either:\n\n* **Completed** — the sale went through successfully\n* **Voided** (red badge) — the sale was reversed after the fact\n\nClick any **Sale ID** to open the full [Sale Details panel](#sale-details).\n\nClick any **Client name** to open their [Client Profile](#client-profile).\n\n***\n\nPayments [#payments]\n\n**Sales → Payments**\n\nEvery payment transaction that was successfully collected — similar to Sales Transactions but focused on the payment side only. Voided sales are excluded here.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Payment Date · Client · Team Members · Payment Method · Tips · Status · Amount\n\nTips show in the Tips column when they were added to the sale. Search by client name or sale ID, or filter by date range.\n\n***\n\nMemberships [#memberships]\n\n**Sales → Memberships**\n\nAll membership packages that have been sold, with live session tracking.\n\n**Columns:** Purchase Date · Client · Membership name · Service · Sessions (used / remaining with a progress bar) · Cost · Status\n\nThe **Status** shows either **Active** (sessions still available) or **Completed** (all sessions used). The progress bar makes it easy to see at a glance how far through a package a client is.\n\n***\n\nVouchers [#vouchers]\n\n**Sales → Vouchers**\n\nAll vouchers that have been purchased or redeemed. Search by client name, voucher name, or voucher code. Filter by date range to narrow results.\n\n***\n\nProducts [#products]\n\n**Sales → Products**\n\nA record of every product sold, with live stock levels.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Product Name · Category · Brand · Quantity · Unit Price · Total Price · Current Stock · Sale Date · Status\n\nThe **Current Stock** column shows a warning icon (⚠) when stock is running low. The **Status** badge will show **Low Stock** to flag items that need reordering.\n\nSearch by product name, SKU, barcode, or category.\n\n***\n\nTips [#tips]\n\n**Sales → Tips**\n\nEvery tip that's been collected, attributed to the staff member who received it.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Tip Amount · Staff Member · Payment Method · Sale Total · Date\n\nSearch by staff name, payment method, or sale ID. Filter by date range.\n\n***\n\nClient Profile [#client-profile]\n\nAnywhere you see a **client name** shown as a blue link (in Sales Transactions, Payments, etc.), you can click it to open that client's full profile in a panel on the right.\n\nThe profile is split into two parts:\n\n**Left — Client details**\n\n* Name, phone, and email\n* **Edit client** — update their contact details\n* **Add review** — add an internal note or review about the client\n* Date of birth (optional)\n* Date the client was created in the system\n\n**Middle — Navigation tabs**\nSwitch between different views of the client's history:\n\n| Tab          | What it shows                                                      |\n| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| Appointments | All appointments with status badges (Paid, Scheduled, No Show)     |\n| Sales        | All completed sales with service, total, and a View Details button |\n| Products     | Products purchased by this client                                  |\n| Vouchers     | Vouchers associated with this client                               |\n| Memberships  | Active and completed membership packages (shows count badge)       |\n| Loyalty      | Loyalty programme activity                                         |\n\n**Right — Detail view**\nClicking any item in the tabs shows the full detail on the right side. For example, clicking a sale shows the service, time, staff, subtotal, VAT, and total.\n\n***\n\nSale Details [#sale-details]\n\nClicking a **Sale ID** or **View Details** anywhere in the Sales Hub opens the full Sale Details panel. This shows:\n\n* **Status badge** (e.g., Completed)\n* Client name and phone\n* **VAT Invoice** number and date\n* Services performed with time, duration, and assigned team\n* **Staff Information** — assigned staff member and receptionist\n* Subtotal, VAT (5%), and Total\n* **Print icons** — print as thermal receipt or standard A4 invoice\n* **Sale-ID** (copyable)\n* **Void Sale** button — reverses the transaction if an error was made\n* **Back to Appointment** button — returns to the linked appointment\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  Voiding a sale cannot be undone. Only use this if there was a genuine error with the transaction.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Section            | Best used for                                           |\n| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Daily Sales        | End-of-day reconciliation — cash, card, and tips totals |\n| Appointments       | Looking up a specific service or client visit           |\n| Sales Transactions | Full transaction log including voided sales             |\n| Payments           | Collected payments only, with tips                      |\n| Memberships        | Session usage and package status                        |\n| Vouchers           | Gift card purchases and redemptions                     |\n| Products           | Retail sales with live stock levels                     |\n| Tips               | Gratuity records by staff member                        |\n"}